			<p><img src="images\TriangleChokeOpsGotPosture.jpg" alt="TriangleChokeOpsGotPosture" style="float:left"><h1>Triangle Choke When Opponent has good posture</h1>
			Head and arm choke using legs</br>
			Opponent has good posture, you can use this in sequence with hip bump sweeps, kimura, guilotine.</br>
			Same start as other attacks to posture, rotation from 1 side to the other of op to negate their hands controlling your hips</br>
			Go for a hip bump sweep, get op to put an arm out to counter, left hand to back of ops neck, left leg goes high (around middle back), right hand to floor,
			hang your weight off your left arm, this will pull op down a bit, right leg now has no weight and can swing up onto ops left shoulder, this should add
			more weight to op and break their posture, get a loose triangle, grab their arm/head, pull down and adjust the legs to get a tight triangle.</p>
