				<header><h1>Notes</h1></header>
				usually a blood choke but can be tracheal compression restraint (wind choke) if you turn ops head to face thigh</br>
				first defense, keep both arms in or both arms out</br>
				second defense, posture up, get your hips in close, push chest out, pull chest in push arm through hole, cable grip, push ops legs apart</br>
